column2: Put out loon nesting platform with vegetation.
No nesting activity- no sign of a loon.

column1: Students focused on invasive species as it is Invasive Species Awareness Month.  Students also learned about shoreland buffers and took percentage of cover (Canopy- Shrub- Groundcover) for a 100 foot transect from shore - upland.

column2: Windy- sunny- snow has been gone for about a month.  Ice out April 1.  Early leaf out- trees are budding.  Macro Invertebrates collected include dragonfly nymph- scud- midge larva- caddisfly larva- water mite- crawling water beetles and alderfly larva.

Shoreland and aquatic plants collected included wild rice- spadderdock- wild bog cranberries- cotton grass- rattlesnake manna grass.  Removed nesting platform- no loons present- nested naturally 1st attempt- failed- nested on platform 2nd attempt- failed 2 eggs found in tact.
pH reading not taken- probe was broke.
